codex
The StatefulSet uses one secret, `es-http-tls`, for both HTTP and transport TLS, so a direct CA swap could momentarily split transport trust between old and new certs. I’m going to use a phased CA-bundle approach: trust old+new first, then roll new leaf certs, then publish the final client CA once the service is serving the new chain.
